# Shopify Sections Development

## Section Structure
Sections are modular, reusable content areas that can be customized in the theme editor.

## Basic Section Template
```liquid
{% comment %}
  Section: Section Name
  Description: Brief description of the section
{% endcomment %}

<div class="section-{{ section.id }}">
  {% if section.settings.title != blank %}
    <h2>{{ section.settings.title }}</h2>
  {% endif %}
  
  <!-- Section content here -->
</div>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Section Name",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "title",
      "label": "Title",
      "default": "Section Title"
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Section Name"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}

## Setting Types
- `text`: Single line text input
- `textarea`: Multi-line text input
- `image_picker`: Image selection
- `color`: Color picker
- `select`: Dropdown selection
- `checkbox`: Boolean toggle
- `range`: Numeric slider
- `url`: URL input

## Blocks
Use blocks for repeatable content:
```liquid
{% for block in section.blocks %}
  <div {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
    <!-- Block content -->
  </div>
{% endfor %}
```

## Best Practices
- Always include a schema
- Use semantic HTML
- Make sections responsive
- Include proper accessibility attributes
- Use meaningful setting IDs
- Add presets for easy setup
